            "!Elizabeth IV<br>modI think now is a good time to teach you <br>modabout defense.<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>modThis is your shield, useful for blocking and<br>modparrying enemy attacks. It takes 1 stamina<br>modpoint to use. <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modLet’s start by blocking an attack.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modTo block an attack, simply raise your shield<br>modby holding down the $$input007  <br>modReady?<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modGO!<br>mod<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modGood!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modBear in mind that your shield is not<br>modindestructible, so every time you block it <br>modwill deteriorate. <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modTake too many hits and it will break! <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modYou can fix your shield with magic anvils, <br>modplus you can check your shield’s health in <br>modthe items menu.<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modThere’s a better way to use your shield <br>modwithout breaking it, it’s called parrying. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modIt consists of raising your shield right <br>modbefore an enemy hits you, and BOOM!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modNow your enemy is stunned and <br>modvulnerable to attacks! <br>modPlus, you regain a little stamina too!<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modLet’s try it out, ready?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modGO!<br>mod<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modSo satisfying! <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modThis is THE best strategy against your <br>modenemies. Try to memorize their attacks so<br>modyou can counter them like a pro! <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modUnlike blocking, parrying doesn’t damage <br>modyour shield so be careful when attempting <br>modthis!<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modLast but not least, you can also use parry <br>modto send back certain projectile attacks <br>modfrom your enemies!<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modEnough chit-chat, use your shield to <br>moddefeat that monster!<br>mod",
            "!Elizabeth IV<br>modI think now is a good time to teach you <br>modabout defense.<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>modThis is your shield, useful for blocking and<br>modparrying enemy attacks. <br>modIt costs 1 stamina point to use. <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modLet’s start by blocking an attack.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modTo block an attack, simply raise your shield<br>modby holding down the $$input007  <br>modReady?<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modGO!<br>mod<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modGood!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modThat green circle represents your shield's <br>modlife, and it seems like it took some damage<br>modalready.<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modTake too many hits and it will break!  <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modYou can fix your shield with magic anvils  <br>modoutside of battles in your items menu.  <br>modOr pay to fix it in the evil store.  <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modThere’s a better way to use your shield <br>modwithout breaking it, it’s called parrying. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modIt consists of raising your shield right <br>modbefore an enemy hits you, and BOOM!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modNow your enemy is stunned and <br>modvulnerable to attacks! <br>modPlus, you regain a little stamina too!<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modLet’s try it out, ready?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modGO!<br>mod<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modSo satisfying! <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modUnlike blocking, parrying doesn’t damage <br>modyour shield. AND it can even send back  <br>modmost projectile attacks!  <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modYou can even parry and block while tired!  <br>modEspecially useful when you're in a pinch.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modEnough chit-chat.<br>modDefeat that monster!<br>mod",
            "!Elizabeth IV<br>modI bet you’re tired of attacking like a chump, <br>modam I right?<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>modMeet your hammer! This is a pretty heavy <br>modattack, so it takes a lot of time to perform <br>modbut it deals a whole lot of pain!<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modTo use your hammer, press the $$input008  <br>modAre you ready?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modGO!<br>mod<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modNow you’re playing with power!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modThis attack uses a whopping 6 points of<br>modstamina, so you better upgrade it if you<br>modwant to use it regularly.<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modYou can hold your attacks if you keep the<br>modhammer button pressed down!<br>modJust like the sword and the slingshot.<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modWell!<br>modThat’s about it, continue the fight!<br>mod",
            "!Elizabeth IV<br>modHold up, kid! <br>modYou see that weird artifact over there?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modThose were put there by ancient beings to<br>modaid the chosen one and yours truly in our<br>modquest to defeat evil.<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modThe same beings that created me.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modThese eerie statues can record our <br>modprogress as soon as we pass them.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modTo avoid losing progress, I recommend <br>modusing Save Stations if you plan on <br>modswitching save files.<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modYou got all that, scarf boy?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<hero><br>mod<br>mod?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modI-I mean… kid. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modKeep that in mind, kid.<br>mod",
            "!Elizabeth IV<br>modHey… <br>modI think we can use the elevator now.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modLet’s have a chat with that hairy menace.<br>mod",
