            "!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modBack from the dead, huh? <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modEven though it might seem like a disaster,<br>modthis actually worked out in our favor, for<br>modonce…  <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modNow that everything is flooded we can just<br>modswim to the top! <br>modNo wall jump, no elevator...<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modWhat a profound waste of time.<br>mod",
            "!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modAnother blizzard!?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Bella<br>mod<br>modThis is not an ordinary b-blizzard… <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Bella<br>mod<br>modThis has something to do with the Baron.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modGreat. <br>modAt least we know he’s home.<br>mod",
            "!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod…Ow, what happened?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modAre these… triviality stones? <br>modWhat is going on here…<br>mod",
            "!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod...!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modIs that… THE HERO!?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Grey Kid<br>modI think he’s alive! <br>modGive me a sec, I’m trying to set him free!<br>mod<pg>Elizabeth IV<br>modHero! Scarfy! <br>modIt’s me, Elizabeth! Can you hear me!?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Hero<br>mod<br>modUgghh- Eli…zabeth?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modYES! It’s me!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Hero<br>mod<br>modDo I… know you?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modHuh?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Hero<br>modOw, my head… where am I? <br>modThis doesn’t seem like… home?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod…You really don’t remember me.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Hero<br>mod<br>modNo… I’m sorry. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Grey Kid<br>mod<br>modI always knew you were a useless hero…  <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Hero<br>modI am a… hero? <br>modBut I don’t even know how to fight! <br>modWhat is going on here!?<pg>T. Bur<br>mod<br>modYou finally found him, huh? <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modYOU! What is the meaning of this!? <br>modHe survived!? How is this possible!?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modOh no, no, you misunderstand. <br>modHe was pretty dead when I found him. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modThat Masked Kid really did a number on <br>modthat hero model.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modYou... mean this kid really killed the...<br>modhero? But...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modOf course! Think about it, do you really <br>modthink 745 had any choice in the matter? <br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modThe hero was coming, death was certain! <br>modIt was all or nothing, kill or be killed.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<hero><br>mod<br>mod...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod...It just...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modIt doesn’t make it right!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modI don’t know what right or wrong is <br>modanymore. I just want to protect Stitches <br>modfrom himself.<nl>!MOD!Grey Kid<br>modWhoa, back up. <br>modYou mean this is the same hero that died <br>moda few days ago?<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modThe one and the same. <br>modWe repurpose him every so often so he <br>modcan fulfill the cycle of the hero.  <nl>!MOD!Handy<br>mod<br>mod!!!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Bella<br>modYou m-mean, he was revived like the <br>modBaron?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modThe Baron was our first hero model, yes. <br>modBut Greg was a failure, I’m afraid. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modHe defeated Mr. Stitches like he was <br>modsupposed to, but he had too much...<br>modfree will. <nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modYears later, he discovered that <br>modMr. Stitches was still alive, and challenged <br>modhim to a duel.<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modMr. Stitches killed him that time, of course, <br>modand I had to revive him while erasing his<br>modmemories. <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modGreg...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modWhat is that “cycle” you keep babbling <br>modabout!? <br>modTalk!!<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>mod*Sigh* This is why I didn’t want to do this <br>modexperiment in the first place, so much<br>modexplaining! <nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modBut Mr. Stitches insisted on it. <br>modHe is so interested in the outcome.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Hero<br>mod<br>modI have no idea what is going on here.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>mod“The hero cycle” to put it simply, is the <br>modjourney heroes embark on to defeat evil. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modEvil is defeated, years pass, evil emerges <br>modagain as well as a new hero.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modWe are in charge of recreating the hero’s<br>modjourney, again and again.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modTo that end, Stitches needed an army, a <br>modchallenge for the hero. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modHe asked me to clone our old comrades, <br>modand keep the originals here so they could<br>modbe safe.<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modThe hero fights hordes of clones that we <br>modhave to revive time and time again.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<hero><br>mod<br>mod!!!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modYou are a… clone!?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>mod<br>modClone 745, to be precise. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modI really don’t know what caused such an<br>modanomaly, but 745 acted on its own accord,<br>moddisrupting the hero cycle in the process.<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modAre Tim and Timbolt a clone, too!?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modKing Timothy? Oh no, he wandered here <br>modby mistake and saw things he shouldn’t <br>modhave.<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modI had to erase his memory, but something<br>modwent wrong and his mind was split in two. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modWe couldn’t let him go back to the Moth <br>modQueen in this broken state. So we keep <br>modhim here, until I find a way to fix him.<nl>!MOD!Grey Kid<br>modWhy do you keep… recreating this story!?<br>modWhat is the POINT?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>mod<br>modIf we don’t continue the cycles...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>mod<br>modThe world will cease to exist.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Grey Kid<br>mod<br>mod*Gasp*<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>mod…Or at least that’s what Mr. Stitches <br>modbelieves. I’ve always been a skeptic, but <br>modI respect my friend’s beliefs. <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modI don’t buy this crap! I’m a legendary <br>modweapon created to-<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>mod-aid the heroes on their journeys. The <br>modstatues that you have found on your <br>modtravels only react when you are close.<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modThey provide accurate data about you and<br>modthe hero’s progress. It also works as a <br>modbackup when we want to restart a hero. <nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modYou mean… the ancient beings that <br>modcreated me were a lie? <br>mod...It was all you?<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modYou are Elizabeth 1.4! <br>modOnce every cycle ends we erase your <br>moddata so you can restart anew!<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod...This is why I can’t remember anything <br>modfrom... before.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modYour purpose is to absorb the power of <br>modthe clones. You were designed to defeat<br>modStitches, but never kill him. <nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modOr, at least that’s how it works with the <br>modheroes I designed. They’re as strong as I<br>modallow them to be. <nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modBut this kid you’ve been traveling with...<br>modhas no restraints, no inherent limits set <br>modby me. <nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>mod745 has unlocked a greater power within <br>modyou, more than you’re supposed to have.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modYou now have enough power to face <br>modMr. Stitches, and there’s a slight <br>modprobability of you killing him. <pg>Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modAnd even if the possibility is slim, I have <br>modto stop you. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!T. Bur<br>modI will not let you hurt my friend or escape<br>modthis place.<br>mod<pg>Grey Kid<br>mod<br>modI… can’t believe this… <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod...Everything I’ve ever known is a lie.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Bella<br>mod...If we stop this cycle, do you r-really <br>modthink the world could end?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Grey Kid<br>modI feel so USED! <br>modI was able to break free and come this <br>modfar... and it was all for nothing!?<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod…What do you mean, break free?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Grey Kid<br>mod<br>mod...<br>mod<pg>Cereza<br>mod<br>mod...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>mod!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Bella<br>mod<br>modThe p-princess!?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Cereza<br>modI was kidnapped, and when I was no<br>modlonger useful to Stitches he let me go. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Cereza<br>modBut I just wanted to save my kingdom...<br>modI wanted to take the legendary weapon<br>modso I could kill Stitches myself...<nl>!MOD!Cereza<br>mod...But did I even stand a chance? <br>modIs my kingdom and all its subjects just <br>modpart of this scheme, too?<nl>!MOD!Cereza<br>mod<br>modI... don’t know what to do now...<br>mod<pg>Tester<br>modTest Line 1<br>modTest Line 2<br>modTest Line 3<nl>!MOD!Tester<br>modTest Line 1<br>modTest Line 2<br>modTest Line 3<nl>!MOD!Tester<br>modTest Line 1<br>modTest Line 2<br>modTest Line 3<nl>!MOD!Tester<br>modTest Line 1<br>modTest Line 2<br>modTest Line 3<nl>!MOD!Tester<br>modTest Line 1<br>modTest Line 2<br>modTest Line 3<nl>!MOD!Tester<br>modTest Line 1<br>modTest Line 2<br>modTest Line 3<nl>!MOD!Tester<br>modTest Line 1<br>modTest Line 2<br>modTest Line 3<nl>!MOD!Tester<br>modTest Line 1<br>modTest Line 2<br>modTest Line 3",
