            "!Elizabeth IV<br>modIt seems like these guys don't work<br>modunderwater.<br>mod",
            "!<br>modThe first time I noticed Stitches not being <br>modquite well, was right after he freed us<br>modfrom our old Queen. <nl>!MOD!<br>modAt first he was happy, but a few days <br>modlater he started rambling about… very <br>modunsettling things that could happen…<nl>!MOD!<br>modUnforeseen consequences of what he had<br>moddone.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modWhere did these ideas come from?<br>modDid the Queen tell him? <br>mod…Or someone else?<nl>!MOD!<br>modSECRET PASSWORD:\n<br>mod“S-I-H”\n<br>mod",
            "!<br>modOk, I’m done. <br>modI’m ALWAYS forgetting my passwords!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modI’m going to start recording them on my <br>modtrusty Itormons.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modThis door’s password is:  <br>mod“O-D-A-C-O-V-A”  <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>modYou better write these down in your <br>modjournal, kid.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<hero><br>mod<br>mod!<br>mod",
            "!<br>modIt happened again, today. I was about to <br>modenter Mr. Stitches’ chamber, and I heard <br>modhim talking to himself. <nl>!MOD!<br>modHe does this all the time when I’m with <br>modhim… but this time he hadn’t realized I <br>modwas there, and it almost felt like he was…<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>mod...Conversing.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modI could swear I heard a very different <br>modvoice coming from his room.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modThere must be someone, or something… <br>modin there with him. <br>modThis has sparked a number of questions.<nl>!MOD!<br>modWhat is this foreign entity? How long has <br>modit been in contact with Stitches? What <br>moddoes it want? What is it telling him?<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modI need to do further research.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modSECRET PASSWORD:<br>mod“N-I”<br>mod",
            "!<br>modIn order to gather some evidence for my <br>modtheory, I planted a small microphone in <br>modMr. Stitches’ chamber, and waited…<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modBut the other voice did not appear.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modCould this mean it knows what I did? <br>modI’m afraid to even write this down.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modOr maybe… the fact that I’m still alive <br>modproves that it can’t harm me? <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modPerhaps this thing can’t physically <br>modinteract with us.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modMaybe it can only talk to Stitches… Has it <br>modbeen influencing him all this time? <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modCould it be lying to him about the cycles?<br>modAnd its consequences!?<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modI… I can’t prove anything, I’m afraid. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modThis voice, this thing might as well not <br>modexist in our world… I’m the one who <br>modsounds crazy, now.<nl>!MOD!<br>modWithout solid evidence this is all just <br>modconjecture.<br>modStitches could just be insane, after all.<nl>!MOD!<br>modI don’t want to believe it, but the <br>modalternative is too farfetched. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modSECRET PASSWORD:<br>mod“R-E-P-O-L-R-E-T-N-I”<br>mod",
            "!<br>modIf you are reading this, it means I am <br>moddead... <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<hero><br>mod!?!<br>mod<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modNah, just kidding! <br>modThat would be stupid.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modIf someone IS reading this, I’ll just have <br>modto terminate you.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modAnyway! Today I had the most amazing <br>modidea. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modWhen employees die, their energy becomes<br>moda puff of purple smoke that is then sent <br>modback here to regenerate a new minion.<nl>!MOD!<br>modSometimes after many regenerations, <br>modemployees become unstable… <br>modorganically speaking. <nl>!MOD!<br>modBut if I skip the organic matter, I can<br>modrepurpose these guys as intangible blobs <br>modof energy. <nl>!MOD!<br>modAnd then, send them back to Greg’s army <br>modas ghosts! <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modUgh, even I scare myself sometimes with<br>modmy brilliant, cost-effective ideas.<br>mod",
            "!<br>modI’ve modified some employees to fit <br>modcertain criteria, like enhancing their <br>modabilities or elemental powers.<nl>!MOD!<br>modThese enhanced subjects call themselves <br>mod“mini bosses”. I guess they like to sound <br>modimportant. <nl>!MOD!<br>modMini bosses are especially useful when we <br>modwant to test the hero’s abilities.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modI’m always careful not to make them too <br>modstrong, for the hero’s sake. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modIt’s always a hassle when a hero dies...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modAnd they get lost SO easily, too!<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modI can't believe I had to put so many <br>modmaps around the worlds.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modThinking about heroes always gets me<br>modall worked up...<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modAnyway, rant over. <br>modBack to work.<br>mod",
            "!<br>modI needed a way to keep tabs on all the <br>modsubjects. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modThat’s why I created employee cards to <br>modkeep their ID info organized, and to <br>modcharge and pay them on schedule. <nl>!MOD!<br>modFor this, I designed the Booth Ladies and<br>modSave Stations. I needed a friendly face to<br>modtake care of the paper work.<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modPaper work is the worst.<br>mod",
            "!<br>modI lost count of how many times I have <br>modheard “Mr. Stitches has lost his mind”.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modIt angers me that I can’t prove them <br>modwrong about him. He has made difficult<br>modchoices that ultimately lead us here.<nl>!MOD!<br>modDifficult choices that he had to make to <br>modkeep us all safe.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modSo I want to write this down at least <br>modonce, in hopes that I can bring myself to <br>modbelieve it, too.<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modMr. Stitches is not crazy. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modBut there is definitely something wrong   <br>modwith him, and I’m not talking about the <br>modimmense burden that he has to carry. <nl>!MOD!<br>modThere is something else that… compels<br>modhim to act this way. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modI plan on recording my findings, until I <br>modobtain definitive proof for my claims.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modI just want to help my friend.<br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modSECRET PASSWORD:\n<br>mod“D-N-I-M”\n<br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modThat’s some serious denial. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!Elizabeth IV<br>mod<br>modYou better jot these passwords down.<br>mod",
            "!<br>modI designed the Booth Ladies A.I. to be <br>modpretty straight forward: <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modThey encourage employees to save often,<br>modcharge for taxes, and make small talk <br>modfrom time to time. <nl>!MOD!<br>modTo keep them motivated, I added a small <br>moddesire for traveling. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modFor some reason, this caused jealousy<br>modamong the Booth Ladies of different <br>modregions. Very interesting… and sad! <nl>!MOD!<br>modI didn’t even design them with legs... <br>modI think I’ll add that to my to-do list. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>mod<br>modIt will make them happier.<br>mod",
            "!<br>modGenerated subjects are new individuals <br>modaltogether; they have their own identities,<br>modgender and personalities. <nl>!MOD!<br>modBest part? They can even get together <br>modand start families. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modIt’s all a cohesive ecosystem of <br>modself-generating employees. <br>modSuper cheap, too!",
            "!<br>modAfter what happened with Greg, I <br>modperfected the method of erasing memories <br>modwithout damaging the rest of the subject.<nl>!MOD!<br>modFrom now on, trained and tested <br>modemployees have their memories erased <br>modbefore I send them out of the factory.<nl>!MOD!<br>modOnce they’re out, I assign them an ID <br>modnumber, an apartment and a job to do. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modNo one seems to be emotionally broken <br>modbecause of it, so mission successful. <br>mod<nl>!MOD!<br>modExcept for the moth, of course… <br>modI apologize for that, I will fix it... <br>modIt’s in my to-do list.",
